Colombia Had a Budget Surplus of 2.6% of GDP in First Half

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-10-13T17:50:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/colombia-had-a-budget-surplus-of-2-6-of-gdp-in-first-half.html
Colombia  posted a consolidated
budget surplus of 2.6 percent of gross domestic product in the
first half of 2011, compared to a 0.1 percent deficit in the
year earlier period.  The central government had a budget surplus of 1.3 percent
of GDP in the first six months of the year, after posting a 0.8
percent deficit in 2010, according to a statement from the
 Finance Ministry .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrea Jaramillo at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net  